						               													<description>SEVEN is a tile-stacking game that uses polyhexes of 4 hexagons, called tetrahexes. There are 7 different tetrahexes (hence the name of the game).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players alternate turns placing one of their tiles according to some simple rules, trying to get the most of their pieces on the topmost layers when the game ends.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The rules also include a variant and some puzzles.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This stand alone expansion contains the same components as the base game, but in red and blue:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;- 7 red tetrahexes&amp;#10;- 7 blue tetrahexes&amp;#10;- cotton case&amp;#10;&amp;#10;As a standalone product, it allows 2 player games, just like the base game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;As an expansion, it allows two types of gameplay:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;- 3 player&amp;#10;- 2 vs 2 players; with pairs sitting in front of each other.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game has been proven to be non-suitable for 4 player games (too chaotic), hence the 2 vs 2 game mode.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
